# UI stack (MiRoot)

Shell: **ViewBinding** (`ActivityMainBinding`) + **ViewPager2** + **FragmentStateAdapter** (`MainPagerAdapter`). Some flows are **Compose** (`ComponentActivity` + `setContent`). Do not fork parallel “which tab is selected” state.

## Main tabs (single source of truth)

Authoritative selection: **`ViewPager2.currentItem`** (0–4), kept in sync with **`BottomNavigationView`** via `registerOnPageChangeCallback` and `syncingNavFromPager` in `MainActivity`. When adding features that depend on “current tab”, read from the shell (Activity / shared VM / intent extras), do not duplicate indices inside Compose.

| `position` | Fragment | Menu `@id` |
|---:|---|---|
| 0 | `PermissionFragment` | `nav_status` |
| 1 | `FeaturesFragment` | `nav_features` |
| 2 | `MusicFragment` | `nav_music` |
| 3 | `ThemeFragment` | `nav_theme` |
| 4 | `MoreFragment` | `nav_more` |

Menu order: `app/src/main/res/menu/main_nav_menu.xml`. Adapter: `com.wmqc.miroot.ui.main.MainPagerAdapter`.

## Defaults for new work

- **New full screen** (little coupling to pager): prefer **`ComponentActivity` + Compose**.
- **New UI inside a tab**: prefer **`Fragment` + `ComposeView` / `setContent`** in that tab’s fragment, or evolve existing XML if the change is small.
- **Embedding**: Compose in XML → `ComposeView` / `Fragment.setContent`. Legacy View inside Compose → `AndroidView` / `AndroidViewBinding` (not “instead of” Fragment; pick one boundary per screen).

## State & lifecycle

- **ViewPager2** uses `offscreenPageLimit` (see `MainActivity`); distant pages may be **destroyed**. Survive tab switches with **`ViewModel` scoped to the activity** (`activityViewModels()` / `ViewModelProvider(requireActivity())`) or repositories, not only `remember {}` without a store.
- **Deep links / “open tab N”**: handle in **`MainActivity`** (or one coordinator), then `setCurrentItem` + matching bottom-nav id so pager and bar never diverge.

## Interop & legacy

- Prefer **ViewModel / repository / explicit callbacks** over new uses of **`MainActivity.getCurrentInstance()`**; existing Java/Kotlin call sites may keep it for shell commands or legacy broadcasts—new code should not add more static coupling unless unavoidable.
- Cross-feature UI signals already use patterns like **broadcasts** with package-scoped `Intent`s (e.g. music projection); follow that style for “main app ↔ secondary Activity” events instead of inventing a second channel.

## Migration

- Migrate a tab to Compose when **that area** needs sustained UI work; do not block features on a full shell rewrite.
- Parity first (behavior, permissions, saved settings), then visuals.

## Quick checklist (new feature)

- [ ] Tab index / route not duplicated in Compose-only state.
- [ ] Long-lived state uses activity-scoped VM or repo if the page can be off-screen destroyed.
- [ ] Intent/deeplink tab switches go through the same path as user bottom-nav taps.
